2.10	NAC_Stadion	NAC Stadion	NAC Stadion was a multi-use stadium in Breda, Netherlands. It was used mostly for football matches and hosted the home matches of NAC Breda. The stadium was able to hold 20,000 people and opened in 1940. The stadium's capacity was gradually reduced to 10,850 in the nineties, due to security reasons. The stadium was closed in 1996 when the Rat Verlegh Stadion opened.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/NAC_stadium_Beatrixstraat.jpg/250px-NAC_stadium_Beatrixstraat.jpg
